The '''ecoregions of Bhutan''' generally vary according to altitude and precipitation. [[Bhutan]] occupies {{convert|38,394|km2|mi2}}<ref name=official>{{cite web|url=http://www.bhutan.gov.bt/government/aboutbhutan.php |title=National Portal of Bhutan |publisher=Department of Information Technology, Bhutan |accessdate=2011-08-22 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120423102833/http://www.bhutan.gov.bt/government/aboutbhutan.php |archivedate=2012-04-23 |df= }}</ref> in the [[eastern Himalaya]], at altitudes ranging from {{convert|97|m|ft}} to {{convert|7,570|m|ft}}.<ref name=cia>{{cite web|url=https://www.cia.gov/library/publications/the-world-factbook/geos/bt.html |work=[[World Factbook]] |publisher=[[Central Intelligence Agency|CIA]] |title=Bhutan |date=2011-03-22 |accessdate=2011-04-03}}</ref> The dry, plain-like valleys of western and central Bhutan tend to be relatively densely populated and intensely cultivated. The wetter eastern valleys, however, tend to be steeper, narrower ravines.<ref name=LP>{{cite book|title=Bhutan |series=Country Guides |first1=Lindsay |last1=Brown |first2=Stan |last2=Armington |edition=3 |publisher=[[Lonely Planet]] |year=2007 |page=181 |isbn=1-74059-529-7 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=s-L8NUlW_QgC |accessdate=2011-10-15}}</ref><ref name=BoB>{{cite book|title=The Blessings of Bhutan |first1=Russell B. |last1=Carpenter |first2=Blyth C. |last2=Carpenter |publisher=University of Hawaii Press |year=2002 |pages=7–8, 27, 123 |isbn=0-8248-2679-5 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=Liipc-cZpkkC |accessdate=2011-10-15}}</ref><ref name=HKB>{{cite book|title=Himalayan Kingdom Bhutan: Tradition, Transition, and Transformation |first=Awadhesh Coomar |last=Sinha |publisher=Indus |year=2001 |isbn=81-7387-119-1 |pages=20–21 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=rDxx_ibIwZ0C |accessdate=2011-10-15}}</ref> At lower and middle elevations, [[Indomalayan]] biomes range from tropical and subtropical forests to temperate coniferous forests. In the northern mountainous regions, Bhutan is largely [[Palearctic]], comprising [[temperate coniferous forests]], [[montane grasslands and shrublands]], and swaths without any ecozone in its highest glacial elevations.<ref name=WWFmap/>

