{{Infobox Organization |name = The TerraMar Project |image = Terramar-logo.png |image_border = |size = 200px |caption = The TerraMar Project logo |motto = ''Sea Hope. Sea Change. Sea Future.'' |formation = |type |status = |purpose = Protection of oceans |headquarters = New York, New York |region_served = Global |leader_title = Founder |leader_name = [[Ghislaine Maxwell]] |website = [http://theterramarproject.org http://theterramarproject.org] }}
'''The TerraMar Project''', based in [[New York, New York]], is an [[environmentalist]] [[non-profit organization]] involved in protecting the world's oceans.<ref>{{cite web|title=About The TerraMar Project|url=http://www.theterramarproject.org/about|accessdate=4 April 2014}}</ref>
== History ==
TerraMar was founded in September 26, 2012 at the Blue Ocean Film Festival and Conservation Conference in Monterey, California, and focuses on the 64% of the ocean that lies outside any single country's jurisdiction.<ref>{{cite web|last=Platt|first=John|title=TerraMar Project launches to celebrate and protect the world's oceans|url=http://www.mnn.com/lifestyle/eco-tourism/stories/terramar-project-launches-to-celebrate-and-protect-the-worlds-oceans|publisher=Mother Nature Network|accessdate=4 April 2014}}</ref> Their mission is to create a "global ocean community" based around the idea of shared ownership of the global commons, also known as the high seas or international waters.{{CN|date=June 2016}}
